review: before i write the review let me say that i purchased a bottle from a salon in the eu to make sure it was fresh  i cannot attest to the seller here  in general i would be careful before buying salon products through amazon sellers although a review below says that heshe saw no differencenow onto the shampoofirst this is the first cosmetics brand that i use that is actually concerned about its sustainability of its practices and is not just greenwashing  for example they have committed to zeroimpact packaging offsetting their carbon impact by planting trees in italy costa rica and madagascar  moreover their shampoo at least this one is paraben and sulfate free as a person that is concerned about the fact that with respect to the impact on human health and the environment the cosmetic industry is not really overseen in many countries especially the us it is great to know that the davines are also concerned with not throwing in shtty ingredientsnow even given all of this all i need to say is that this is the best shampoo i have ever used  my hair basically looks like a wig now  this is to say it is lustrous smooth free from residue almost superhuman  although there is a small amount in this bottle it is best anyway i think is to reduce your shampooing to no more than  a week to use it after your hair is drenched in water rub the shampoo between your wet hands to get a lather and then rub it very very thoroughly through all parts of your scalp and then rinse very thoroughly  in my experience the conditioner you use after doesnt really mattermy hair type is a large quantity of very fine strands previously it was somewhat dry and oily

review: my hair is very thick and has just enough curl to it that once its dry it turns a bit frizzy and flips around in weird ways  i like to have it straightened and tamed to give it body and shape without being stiff and stick straight typically i started with a blow dryer and a paddle brush following this up with a flat iron to get that sleek silky smooth look  then i use a largebarrel curling iron to give it some shape  i really hate using all this heat on my hair though due to the damage i know it can cause  i try very hard to keep my hair as healthy as possible and as a result i get frequent comments from hair salons about how healthy my hair is i even kept my hair cut into a long pixie cut for the last couple of years just to avoid having to use all these damaging heat tools on it when its short enough it curls nicelylately ive been growing my hair back out and last week my old hair straightener gave up the ghost i took this opportunity to order the perfecter after being introduced to it by my sister a few months ago  using this tool alone my hair looks the best it has done in months  the perfecter is far better than i ever would have believed prior to using it  i am absolutely thrilled

review: this is the first time i am using  a double edge razor i was worried that shaving with a de would be difficult but this was not so did not cut myself at all if you are transitioning from disposable razors the first thing you notice about this short handle merkur is the weight it is much heavier than the multi blade disposables it is however very balanced another thing that is different is the size of the shaving head which is quite large compared to the disposable multi blades my facial bone structure is small im only  lbs so the size of the shaving head was a challenge but i adapted quickly when you use this razor dont press hard or you will most definitely cut yourself remember it does not pivot let the weight of the razor do the work be very careful at the jawline and other bony parts of your face the blade provided is very smooth and cuts well you can go against the grain once the initial hairs have been removedi am glad i transitioned to de shavingmuch less expensive than the multi blades with the same or even better results

review: darn near perfectthe cases along with lowquality items are generally what sink items like thisto save money the manufacturer will often use items that are very middle of the road at best to keep the overall cost down kind of like the difference between buying a dinette set with chairs included or buying everything separatelyand then there is the case they quickly cobbled together to hold the items which is usually falling apart even before opening the package letting items slip out through large gaps or bang together and get scratchedfor this kit they took a flagship item their collapsable nail clippers and packaged it with other useful items in a fantastically good casethe nail clippers are fantastic theyve been around for years now and with good reason they are nickelthin when put away super sharp and easy to use there is a little trick to pulling out the handle and setting it into the detent so if your clippers arent closing all the way keep playing with it once you figure this out it is trivial to pull them out use them and put them away they are so good that i use them as my regular clippers not just for travelingthe case is neatly organized prevents items from banging together and slipping out is well made and small enough to easily slip into a dopp kit while traveling if you get a splinter or break a nail theyve got you covered my only quibble is with the metal file because personally i think metal files rough up the nail more than file them but every kit is like thatthis would also make a nice selfcontained gift for someone going off to college or an overseas triprecommendedsean logue

review: i dont often ding a product for its price after all prices here are in a constant state of flux and everyone has a different definition of what is expensive or too much money for me to righteously make a judgement call  so i wont bring down my rating of this brush because of its current priceit may be different tomorrowi wont even ding this brush for its claims to microexfoliate  whos to say  im no expert but i do know that using a gentle rotating brush on a motorized handle is just fine and very helpful  whats to say that a makeup brush cant do some minimal exfoliating too  so if this company wants to give this brush some hardtodefineandanalyze capabilities i say go right ahead  i wont debate it with you  which does not mean that i buy into the hoopla but that it is not what i am concerned about in a makeup brushwhat i will say is this  this brushs bristles and the thickness of the bristles and the trim work on the bristles is superior in quality and workmanship  it is a beautiful matte black brush with good balance and a bulge in a perfect place for my thumb and two fingers to grab hold  and this brush reminds me of the size shape and thickness of my koreanstyle brush set  and i love that set for its thick bristles thick handle and short stature  this is a better quality thoughby a long shotthis brush is very easy to hold and not fatiguing  its short handle makes it easy to be very exact with my application  and the thick concentration of very fine and soft bristles grab hold of foundation blush and concealers  but when i apply it to my face the bristles release their contents smoothly and evenlyi could not ask for more from a brush and i think that a quality brush like this will last a long time with proper tlc and proper cleaningwhat i hoped for but was disappointed to find missing  instructions for proper use and cleaning procedures and more info on the ambiguous claims  it would have been nice to learn how to achieve the results that this scottvincent borba line promises  but i can wing it well enough because its a really great brush
product: scottvincent borba antifatigue foundationcontour brush and line smoothing microexfoliation tool

review: i gave this stuff  stars because i love the color and the smell is nice compared to most tanners out there self tanners have a reputation of showing up very orange on me and this is the closest ive ever gotten to a natural more brown color with a self tanner the tan is also not overdone even when left on for the maximum amount of time its almost like it works with your skin tone to give you the most believable color possible as opposed to something too deep that could look fake or overdone for the reference i am pretty fair complected with goldenred undertones and can tan in the sun without burning but i dont get incredibly darknow on to the reason for the omission of  star this stuff can be streaky i dont know why but it seems like it takes a lot of product to achieve results and i have tried multiple application methods and all have left me with streaks some minor some more noticeable personally i dont like the mitt that seems to make the streaking worse the best application for me is straight bare hands but wash your hands immediately i once applied what i thought was a good amount of the product only to achieve very very little color i had followed the directions and exfoliated too i find the best color is acheived when i apply shortly after showering as opposed to showering at night and then applying in the morning

review: i am a needlework designer who works with her hands in various fibers throughout the day  the results is very dry skin on my hands  i also have a tendency to develop hang nails that ingrow and my dermatologist has told me the way to avoid both is to keep my hands moisturized  i have been using a very expensive shea moisturizer but decided to try the ahava cream to see how it worked  i was surprised to discover that it works almost as good as a hand cream that cost more than five times as much  as i have to continually reapply the cream after i wash my hands and i do that many times a day especially when i am taking care of my toddler grandson this amounts to a great amount of savings  with this product and others i find i do have to wash it off when i am actually working with fibers so i dont get the oils on them and discolor them  there are some products that works okay with fibers but they usually have lanolin in them and i cant use themmy plan is to use this product throughout the day and to apply the shea product for overnight  that way i get the value of both in the best way

review: a rich blend of citrus dry herb and wood artisan reminds me of a slightlyyounger more hip version ofnbspa datahookproductlinklinked classalinknormal  bahamas signature colognea  while the item description spends a lot of time talking about the beauty of the rattanwrapped bottle etc etc thats not going on a date with me so i wanted to know how it smells and how it laststhe scent has top notes of semisweet citrus like blood orange or tangelo  its not the overthetop sweetness of anbspa datahookproductlinklinked classalinknormal  klein colognea but the subtle masculine take varvatos is famous for this is further cut by wood and dry herb midnotes using majoram thyme and ginger in place of the more common tobacco leaf patchouli and musks  this makes a cologne with a sharp initial hit and heavy in its midrange but without the musky bottom of anbspa datahookproductlinklinked classalinknormal all of which should be fantastic butthis cologne faded really quickly and not in a colognevseau way  having tested the same cologne atnbspa datahookproductlinklinked classalinknormal  im stunned at how watereddown the bottle from amazon seems  having worked with highend colognes sales in my past this can happen if the incoming supplier does something shady like actually water down the product or more likely in this case if the product is being warehoused poorly with temperatures and age deteriorating its potency  ill give ammy the benefit of the doubt and hope its the latterto be clear varvatos has yet again created a brilliantly good mens cologne  just maybe pick it up someplace else

review: love this ive used practically everything out there proactiv prescription creams clinique you name it and mario badescus drying lotion works the best by farwhen i break out its usually in tiny patches around my temples or mouth a small dab of this at night dries up whiteheads and smoothes out those annoying red bumps and lumpsheres a timeline of what you can expect the morning after each application based on my experience yours might be differentday  nothing be patientday  your whiteheads will be significantly smaller a small dry circle of skin will remain on top of your old whitehead which is easily washed off and you should follow up with toner tooday  the acne patch will be much flatter maybe even completely flat the area will remain red but now that its flat you can easily conceal the areaim guessing it takes more than a few days of applying the product to fade red spots all in all highly recommend

review: i really needed a new shaving gelcream  well lets put it this way  ive always been searching because everything i ever bought was worse than the next  my face and especially my neck got sliced up  how i hated shaving  i couldnt help but notice how many rave reviews were written about this shaving soap  i was very skeptical at first  the last soap i used was williams and let me tell you that was the last one for a reason  i decided to take my old badger brush out of retirement and go back to the nostalgic way  when i first applied the lather i was a little suprised and worried how thin the film was but when the blade starting gliding i was very happy  the menthol has a very cooling effect which is such a relief  the level of protection is great just as long as you dont apply too much pressure with your double edge razor but im sure you already knew that  if you miss a spot or want to touch up no problem  you can just brush on some more  some people might look at the price and think wow  for shaving soap  trust me ive been using this for a month everyday and i havent even burned through the half way point  it lasts and its worth every penny  get yourself a good brush a brush stand a double edge razor and throw out that overpriced one sharp blades and a lathering bowl  keep in mind a double edge razor is sharper and gives you a much closer shave than those rip off razors  after you get the hang of it youll never go back  even women should try this  the experience will speak for itself  ive tried almost everything and nothing comes close to this  shaving is enjoyable and i nick myself much less these days  the ingredients make your skin feel nice and soft and not screaming with irritation  take your time and enjoy it  for an added bonus buy the green proraso after shave oil

review: i was so tired of paying too much money for the standard disposable cartridges that i finally took the plunge into the de razor world and i have to tell you ill never go backnever  ive been shaving with the new razor now for  months  i waited a while to make a review so that i could really assess the experience  first off shaving is now an experience  its not something to nail out in the shower in  minute and rush off to work  now that im proficient with the razor it will take me on average just under  minutes to shave if im starting from a cold dry face warming up the water creating a lather with the soap putting a hot towel on my face to open the pores shaving aftershave  im sure that sounds like a lot of extra work but i will tell you its one of the best parts of my day now  i am eager to shave and at the end i have a baby smooth face that smells out of this world  because the blades are so inexpensive i never hesitate to toss a new one in and have the perfect shave every timei would suggest watching videos and looking up techniques  i tried some different things and this is what i found to be the best approach shower first because it really opens your pores prior to shaving  a hot wet towel will work but not as good ive used the cheaper van der hagen shave soap and the taylor of bond street  cheap worked just fine for me get a variety pack of blades because they make a huge difference and it seems to depend on your face  for me the feather blades have beaten out the  other kind in my pack  they are amazing for me but you have to find what works for you and if you just get one type of blade and it sucks you will probably never use the razor take your time to shave properly  if you need to occasionally rush out the door keep a disposable on hand  i have found that  passes makes a baby smooth shave  pass down   pass inward towards my nose  against the grain up  this razor can go against the grain and that pass gives you the baby smooth shave good aftershave  i have only tried clubman  it smells great gives you that burn that wakes you up and gets you going have a styptic pencil on hand for minor cuts rarethe only times ive cut myself were when i was rushing had a crappy blade or if i had a blemish that the razor caught  by far the latter is the most common  if youre broken out a lot the razor seems to shave so closely that it may cut ive never had a bad cut they have all been very minor  give this thing a try and you will never look at shaving the same again  im sick of corporate american brain washing us into paying more throwing everything away and having a crappier experience  this is the way men should shave
product: merkur classic  razor double edge saftey razor

review: i have sensitive skin and this retinol formula is supposed to be irritation free or at least minimally irritating  i started out using it twice a week and then when absolutely nothing happened i stepped it up to every night  i did this for three weeks and nothing happened  my skin didnt look any different  i know this is a mild formula but surely i would have seen some positive change during this time  i definitely think i received a fake either that or this formula is so mild that it isnt effective at all  im sorely disappointed in this product which was not cheap by any means  im going to order the  formula directly from the avene website and that way ill be assured that its the authentic product  they dont even sell the  formula on the company site so that should have told me something  i guess they dont make it anymore  obviously i received a fake or an expired product because i would have expected some positive change after  weeks of use and zero happened  i wouldnt waste your money on this product  if you want a mild retinol thats suitable for sensitive skin order the  formula directly from the company  i discovered this brand in bazaar magazine which had an article written by a dermatologist in which this sensitive skin retinol formula was touted by the author as being a sensitive skin formula  i always thought i couldnt use retinol at all because i had a bad reaction to retin a years ago as well as a severe reaction to a philosophy retinol serum i tried two years ago  i want the benefits of retinol but my skin cannot handle the irritation i break out in angry red patches and my eyes swell shut  i thought this mild formula was the answer to my prayers  however i spent a significant sum of money only to be duped  this formula did nothing nada  im going to order the  formula directly from avene  im sure it will be a great product because the doctor who mentioned it is quite well know and the article gave the company website as the place to purchase  i will not order another skin care product from amazon  this is the second or third time ive been duped  ive learned an expensive lesson  if you want to try this product dont get it here  i definitely do not recommend whatever is in this bottle  i think its just some greasy cream and whoever sells it has been able to dupe a fancy bottle and pump
product: eau thermale avegravene retrinal  cream  fl oz

review: i have never been one to indulge on grooming products  i usually buy the store brand equivalent of shampoo and when i buy deodorantantiperspirant it is usually a bulk pack of axe or old spice from one of those shopping club stores  however just recently i was turned on to the molton brown line of grooming products specifically their black pepper line  once you get past the initial sticker shock you realize you are dealing with quality products that are a joy to the senses and work as described  while i already had the peppercorn scrub bar and the body wash i decided to pull the trigger and buy the antiperspirant  after only one day of use i knew this was something special and i was hooked  the scent is very distinctive but not overbearing and it literally lasts all day  i have never used a deodorant or antiperspirant in which the scent lasts all day long  in addition it does not irritate the skin it leaves no residue or flakes and leaves you dry all day as well  i never thought i would pay  for antiperspirant but i cannot see myself using anything else now  while i originally bought this directly from molton browns online store it very often sells out there so it is nice to see it here on amazon  if you are on the fence about this go ahead and splurge  you will not regret it

review: i like this meg  antioxidant boost serum  it has a thick silky consistency that goes on smoothly and absorbs rapidly into my skin  i have combination skin and i was happy to find that it left the dry spots hydrated but didnt make the oily spots even oilier  the serum didnt cause any irritation to my hypersensitive skin and my nose only picked up the faintest of scent  i couldnt quite identify the scent  cucumber possibly  if you have ever used elizabeth ardens superstart this boost serum feels a lot like thatlike a thousand other creams the meg  advertises wrinkle and age fighting results but what is intriguing is that the main ingredient supplamine started out as a pharmaceuticals product  like tretinoin retinoic acid retina tazaroc which started out as an acne cream and turned into a blockbuster wrinkle cream or bimatoprost which started out as  eye drops for glaucoma and turned into the eyelash lengthening megahit latisse supplamine was first developed as a treatment in the prevention of kidney disease and blindness in diabetes patientswill meg  turn out to be as effective as retina  only time will tell but im curious enough to use it long turn and test out the effect  i have a lot of creepy skin under my eyes so i will take some before pictures and after a few months of use i will take some after pictures to comparei will update in a few months

review: years ago i had a mason pearson brush that i loved but it was lost somewhere during a move i have had short hair in recent years but am letting it grow it is now mediumshortchin length my concern has been that my hair grow out without split ends which had been my past downfall for long hair  my hair is rather fine and not as dense as it once wasthough not quite thin yet either i wanted to get a boar bristle brush but one look at the current pricing for my favored mason pearsons told me that i could not justify that kind of expenditure so i went looking at alternatives  searching on many sites for ideas and reviews i did not want a combination bristle and nylon brush because i already have an aveda paddle brush that i like and use for stylingthese moroccan oil boar bristle brushes are not much in the webperhaps they are a new addition to their line i like some of the moroccan oil potions though and this brush looked to be good quality and so i ordered itpros great well constructed brush  nice looking and feeling wood handle the mp handle is more lightweight excellent quality bristles it works well on my hair it might be that a lighter handle would be a consideration for anyone with wrist or arthritis issues in their hands i have both but i surely do not think it should be a deal breaker i did my  strikes today with ease this is an excellent brushpotential cons if you have long or thick hair you might well consider getting the combination bristle and nylon brush so that it goes through to your scalp common sense reallyi find that brushing my hair in sections works he best with the all bristle brush all in all i am very happy with this purchase certainly mp brushes have always had a cultlike following and if my resources were limitless i might consider buying one but the fact is that i think we pay somewhat for the name mp as well as the quality all things being equal i feel that this moroccanoil boar bristle brush is a perfect alternative that will last my lifetime with proper cleaning it works probably as well and costs lesswhats not to love

review: i got a generoussized sample of this lotion in a subscription box and now i am trying to justify to myself the expense of purchasing more because its a wonderful product and im almost out of iti didnt see the ingredients on the product page so here they areaqua mineral spring water   cetearyl alcohol ethylhexyl palmitate cetyl alcohol glycerin sodium cetearyl sulfate ethylhexyl methoxycinnamate propanediolcorn derived glycol caprylyl glycol  chlorphenesin  phenoxyethanol maris sal dead sea water dimethicone parfum fragrance aloe barbadensis leaf juice hamamelis virginiana witch hazel flower water alpha isomethyl ionone benzyl alcohol benzyl benzoate benzyl salicylate butylphenyl methylpropional citronellol coumarin geraniol hexyl cinnamal hydroxyisohexyl  carboxaldehyde isoeugenol linaloolfor what its worth a lot of these last ones from citronellol on are compounds produced by plants and found in plant extracts  this doesnt contain parabens which is greati like that this does not include any dyes please note that it does have added fragrance  it has a perfect texture for a body lotion  not too thick and not too thin  ive only been using it on my lower legs   to make it last longer and to get an idea of its effects over time  but the skin on my lower legs is super smooth  this is great to use after shaving your legs and even though i have sensitive skin i found it completely nonirritatingthe smell took a little getting used to  its not bad but its unusual for a body lotion  the perfume level is not heavy at all thoughallinall this is a really nice lotion and i definitely recommend it

review: i should have paid more attention before i ordered this the key ingredient in this is salicylic acid which ive never found to be particularly gamechanging when it comes to my acne and at only  its not a very strong salicylic acid either the first ingredient is water but the second is dimethicone dimethicone is a type of silicone and creates a layer ontop of the skin that can fill and smooth the look of pores wrinkles etc while this can be a desirable feature in a makeup primer i find it odd to see in an acne treatment i also dont really like that the format for delivering the salicylic acid is a lotion i already apply lotion with spf on my face everyday so i dont really want to layer several lotions on my oilyacne prone skin  if this had spf in it then i might consider making it my only lotion however it does not and not using spf isnt an option overall i think this is an ok product but just not right for my particular skin needs i find my acne tends to respond better to tea tree oil and sulfur products such asnbspa datahookproductlinklinked classalinknormal  pure  clear acne treatment gel  ozanbspandnbspa datahookproductlinklinked classalinknormal  care acne spot treatment  ouncea
product: vichy normaderm beautifying salicylic acid acne treatment  fl oz

review: updated i originally reviewed this product as an unsatisfied consumer but i have an entirely new testimonial i was unimpressed with it at first because im so used to traditional curlers i probably only tried actually using this thing about two times before my original review what changed my mind i misplaced the curler i was using again and the japonesque curler was all i had available being determined to curl these lashes i pulled it out and gave it a shot to my surprise my eyelashes curled like ive never seen them curl before yes this item is plasticie but if used correctly it works wonders i will never buy another curler again im hooked seriously my lashes curl so well that i only put eyeliner on my top lid and im good to go no more mascaramy original reviewim a little disappointed in this little curler i lost my favorite eyelash curler a couple weeks ago and have had my eyes on this one for some time now no pun intended i finally made the purchase while i impatiently waited for this to come in the mail didnt take long but i needed something i bought a cheapy  eyelash curler from a local storeto my surprise the  curler works much better than this japonesque curler i used a different curler on each eye to compare the two and unfortunately this curler didnt curl my lashes nearly as well with the money i spent on this one i couldve bought  of my cheapy one

review: i tried the dermablend foundation with the dermablend powder combination several years ago but it always left my face looking caky and dry  then i discovered the maybelline mousse foundation and i switched but ive continued using the dermablend powder on top of my foundation it works fairly well for helping my makeup stay put all day and also for keeping the shine at bay i pat a generous amount of powder on top of my foundation with the puff provided let it settle for a few minutes and then use a large makeup brush to dust all the loose stuff off i prefer the translucent powder to the tinted because it helps even out my skin tone really well it doesnt clog my pores or cause any breakoutsthe issue i have with any powder is that it tends to make my face look well powdery it also makes any fine facial hair stand out  probably most gals over age  can relate to this so what i do after i dust off the powder is to use a hydrating spray i like teddie organics rose water but dont spray your face directly just spray into the air and walk under it letting the fine mist settle on your face youll be amazed at how smooth and creamy your face will look
product: dermablend loose setting powder

review: i use this product where i would otherwise use gold bond or pinaud powdertalc  as others have mentioned it goes on like a lotion but quickly dries i would guess a minute or less into a powder on your skin  it does have a scent but it is light and subtle  the product description says citrus and i would agree  to me it smells like a more subtle and rounded grapefruit scent  so far so good  why i cannot give it higher than a  is performance  at least for me i find that oldfashioned talcpowders just work better at keeping things dry and chafefree  i wanted to really like this product because it is less messy to apply and does smell better than gold bond i like the pinaud scent however but it just doesnt work as well or as long  for me gold bond works the best but smells the worst the spray powder by gb smells great but those cans last for about a week or twonot long enough pinaud smells the best but the talc is a little too fine  either of these work better for me than this product
product: anthony no sweat body defense  fl oz

review: this is a great product i bought it because no matter how many times i go out in the sun my tan has plateaued i have very pale skin even after going to the beach constantly and being out in the sun everyday even when i think that i am finally tan someone will ask me dont you ever go out in the sunthis tanner works amazingly i love the convenience of putting it on in the shower there is no mess whatsoever not even any staining on my rug or towels i turn the shower off step out on to my rug and apply it all over my body its easier to look in the mirror and apply it rather than doing it blindly in the shower it is easy to apply all over the body leaves no streaks and dries pretty quickly i was worried that combined with the water it would drip down my body and onto my rug but i havent had that problem at all i listen to one song on my iphone and by the time the song is over its time to rinse it off the first time i used it i didnt see a difference but after the second time i had a nice color by the next morning i accidentally left in on for about  minutes instead of  i dont know if that affected my end result i cant wait to see how the color develops over timethe smell isnt great it doesnt have a typical selftanner smell atleast the ones im used to but it smells kind of grandmaesque self tanners just dont smell nice however after you rinse it off and dry the smell isnt strong on skin its easily covered with some perfume it seems to have some cat attracting smell in it as well because every time i get out of the shower my siamese kittens come chasing after me trying to eat it maybe its just me i feel like i will run out of this very quickly i end up using  decent sized palmfulls of it for my entire body but the price compared to other self tanners is great i will definitely buy this again i may order the medium one next time instead because the light color is a very subtle change i would definitely recommend trying this its  times better than any ordinary self tanner
product: st tropez gradual tan in shower lotion light

review: background i am  and spent a lot of time in the sun as a teen  i have a lot of fine lines around my eyes eyelids and under eyes and droopy eyelids  i got a hardsell recommendation for this product at the place where i get my botox supposedly the office of a dermatologist  he has dr in front of his name they wanted me to buy it from them for   naturally i wanted to try it somewhere cheaper firstthe middleman seller  i dont have any reason to believe this isnt the real thing  it arrived all sealed up and the red side was candy apple red  it looks just like the product that my botox shop showed methe product  the packaging is a blatant falseadvertising gimmick   ounce would fit in about  this size  i did not detect a bad smell at all  maybe thats an indication that i didnt get the right product but it just didnt smell that bad to me  when my botox clinic gave me a sample on my hand it didnt smell bad to me then either   yes the nozzles dont work that great  store it upside down tap it on your palm a few times before you use it  dont press down in the middle or youll get nothing but the cream  first press on the far right edge to get the red gel to come out and then press on the far left edge to get a matching amount of cream  wipe off the nozzles afterwards so they dont get clogged  you might need to clear the holes with a pin when you first use it  frankly pretty shoddy packaging for the pricethe results  i used this for  weeks religiously day and night  only around my eyes so just a dab of product  after  weeks i did see some minor improvement to the wrinkles  maybe  to  better  but my skin certainly wasnt smooth and wrinklefree and i still had droopy eyelids  ive seen just as good results from far cheaper creams like roc or the vitamin c creams  if youre not looking in a magnifying mirror like i was im not sure anyone else would notice that muchconclusion ok but not worth the price  definitely not worth  and probably not worth   if you look at the youtube video a talk show  i dont know which one theres a guy sitting on stage in scrubs touting the product like hes some kind of medical expert  total hypeill keep using this for  more weeks  if i see startling improvement ill post here againupdate  i continued to use tns for another  weeks morning and night  i saw no additional improvement and my eyes were still wrinkly and crepey so i threw it out  i tried neutragena rapid wrinkle repair and it made my skin burn and turn red and dry out badly and i dont have sensitive skin  about a week after that fiasco i started to use image vital c hydrating serum all over my face and image ageless eye lift creme around my eyes at the advice of the person who does my facials  she did not try to sell me the image products i bought them on amazon so i know it wasnt just product push  this time i definitely saw obvious improvement in a week or so with the fine crepe lines smoothing out a lot and the puffiness diminishing somewhat better but  not gone  in fact i am amazed at how much smoother the skin looks around my eyes  way better than tns  image also moisturizes so my dry skin looks better and rosier all over  everybodys skin is different but if you have old lady crepey skin around your eyes i would definitely recommend image  i would now recommend image over roc
product: skinmedica tns essential serum  oz

review: i ordered my first can of toppick hair building fibers based on the mostly good reviews by other users  i agree that this is a good product  its not great it doesnt make me suddenly look like i have lots of hair but i must say that it is better than the hair i naturally have now  apparently due to aging my once very thick hair has thinned drasically in the past ten years and i have tried many many products in an effort to either regrow hair or to give the illusion of more hair  toppick is applied after shampooing drying and styling and on top of any other hair thickening products  it is a fine powder that is manually shaken from the can toppick is sold in several different color shades and light brown is the first shade that i tried as i have light brown hair with blond highlights neither of which are my natural shade  after the first few shakes i discovered that there were more hair building fibers all over my shoulders shirt and the bathroom than on my head  i invested in the applicator made to fit over the top of the can and i urge anyone who is interested in trying toppick to do the same  the nozzletip applicator makes it much easier and neater to apply this product  the major plusses of toppick are that it hides my shiny pink scalp and i find that the fibers do give the illusion of more hair  the minuses include    i need to use a lot of toppick to achieve the desired results making this product more expensive than i thought it would be   i need to use a special spray to get the fibers to stick in place adding another expense   any time i comb or fix my hair during the day the toppick fibers come out so i need to reapply which is not easily accomplished when not at home and   the powder texture dulls the look of my hair  since the minuses are greater than the plusses for me i gave the toppick hair building fibers light brown only  stars  will i continue to use this product  absolutely  i havent found anything else that hides my naked scalp and gives even a slight illusion of more hair as well as as the toppick fibers  will i continue to use rogaine as well as other thickening and volume building products  absolutely  at least until a magic potion is developed to successfully regrow hair or my vanity weakens  if you are a mature woman and your crowning glory has been reduced to just a few strands i would highly recommend that you give toppick a try just dont make your expecttions too high
product: toppik hair building fibers

review: if youre using razors with multiple blades its the repeated strokes that irritate your skin and cause a rash if youre like me your hair grows in many different directions and a single stroke wont shave off the hairs so youre forced to make a couple of strokes in the same area this product does an amazing job of lifting the hair from the skin and allowing the razor to shave off hair with a single stroke ive tried all the fad shaves and havent been a fan jack black shave products and a schick hydro razor make a shave feel more therapeutic than a  straight razor shave at a barber shop i shave daily so using this product every time i shave could get costly instead i will generally use my jack black shave items on weekends only unless im feeling like i need to pamper myself i recommend coupling it with jack black beard lube conditioning shave  fl oz  and their moisturizing face lotion for the full treatment i wouldnt have ever thought of my self as a guy to leave a review for a bath and beauty product but these products are great and i hope that my review will help another man get as much enjoyment out of a shave as i have with these products yes its expensive but you wont regret your purchase after youve used it

review: if you need a full coverage foundation and you do not have very many facial wrinkles then this cover creme by dermablend may work well for you it is definitely a thick makeup which will help to cover any pigmentation problems however because it is a very thick cream almost as heavy as the average concealer if you have the normal lines and wrinkles on your face that are a result of aging then this foundation may catch in those lines and not give you a smooth finish one of the important things is to blot your skin after the makeup is applied the directions also call for a setting powder however that may also just increase the caking effect in the lines of your skin personally i did achieve a good matte finish with this makeup and did not feel the need for a setting powdersome of the pluses are that it is definitely full coverage if that is what you need and it has a good dose of sunscreen for protection i do have some dark circles under my eyes due to hrt and this cream foundation did a very nice job of hiding them still being over  for everyday wear i found it too heavy to wear on a regular basis and i definitely had trouble with it caking in the lines of my skin my preference is still a good mineral powder foundation for everyday use i know you dont get the full coverage that a foundation of this type can give you but the effect is more natural and lighter especially for daytime use
product: dermablend cover creme full coverage foundation with spf   oz

review: im actually surprised with this razor i always wanted to get this but at the time i had  razors and didnt need it well about  years ago the butterfly broke on a cheap razor i bought and i was down to my edwin jagger  last month my wife dropped it and the stud broke off rendering it trash i decided to get a merkur as a replacement i had forgotten about the  by this time and got model  on the cheap before the razor even made it to the house i was like darn i forgot i wanted to try the slant well i went right back on amazon and ordered it problem is that someone at the distribution center picked a  instead crap amazon quickly sent me the right thing and i just got done mowing  days worth of growth downthis is what i thought from people who talked about this razor the  is an aggressive razor you have to use the weight of the razor only and other potentially life threatening verbiagewhat i ended up experiencing was a razor that i felt was very forgiving glided on my face like silk and gave an outstanding shave i used the normal pressure that i do with any other razor and it just didnt even feel like there was a blade in it i never felt the hair coming off at the end i used barber alum on my face and had absolutely no sting that was the first time that has ever happened in all of my years of using a safety razor and that was after a triple pass shave when i shaved with this i used a brand new feather blade my stubble is not super coarse or thick when it brakes the surface of the skin it kinda coarse but by day  it kinda soft and not really thick i say that because maybe that is why it was good for me and maybe it wont be for someone else i dont really know but i am super impressed and was really surprised at how much of a difference this razor made compared to anything that i used prior makes me just want to keep the  to see how it shaves although im certain the slant was the reason for this improvement
product: merkurrazor safety razor  chrome with slant bar

review: i really liked this product although there are a couple of drawbacks  it dries pretty fast on your skin so if you miss a spot be sure to go back over that area asap so there is no streaking  the product information says that is does not rub off on clothing or sheets  wrong  the color did rub off on my sheets so be ready to wash them immediately  use a stain remover spray on the area and the color will come out of your sheets  i would not recommend sleeping on the sheets again without washing them  the final color after my shower in the morning was a nice medium tan  not too light or dark  if you want a deeper color you need to apply it again  the product was easy to use just a little nerve racking when it comes out of the bottle as it is very dark  i will be using again for my next vacation  happy tanning

review: i chose hot tools after reading the reviews and im really pleased with it  i like that i can adjust the temperature for my hair type so i can curl it without frying it  it has a  degree free spinning cord attachment so the cord never tangles its easycomfortable to hold and use  my hair glides through easily and my hair doesnt get caught or pulled which can be a problem with some irons  this size   is perfect for medium sized spiral curls  my hair is naturally straight on the finer side and has trouble holding a curl but with this iron ive noticed that my curls last pretty much all day  i would recommend this to anyone its a great iron

review: im a woman in my  who has switched to shave soaps  a brush after years of canned foam the proraso green soapcroap is my favorite and the white is very similar both are more of a croap cross between hard cream  soap rather than a straight up hard puck of soap it lathers crazy easily with a wet badger or boar brush  the marco method if youre new to wet shaving or having trouble making lather google it  you wont regret it and provides a good close irritationfree shave i lather in the plastic proraso bowl directly on the soap then go straight to leg i have also done a separate bowl lather with this and it worked nicely after use i leave the lid off for a couple of hours to let the soap dry somewhat i shave in the shower  store my soap there so theres a lot of water and then store it with the lid on the white has a slight menthol feel but considerably less than the green in my opinion the white has a light scent of roses  fresh cut grass its very light and clean and i think it could be considered the most feminine between the green red  white proraso soaps i had issues with irritation from the red proraso disappointing since i loved the scent but neither the green or the white cause any problems for me overall i am extremely pleased with this soap and it will definitely be in my regular rotation

review: i have used mario badescu products for yearsi have often alternated and tried other brands to see if i can duplicate the results i see with this drying lotion but few brands come close the one that comes closest for me is cliniques acne solutions spot healing geli actually keep both on hand in case one type of stubborn pimple reacts better to one than the otherone of the things i love most about mb products is that they have fewer ingredients and do not irritate my skin  whenever possible i try to use more natural products on my skin and i regularly use a variety of cleansing masks along with my clarsonic in order to keep my skin clear  this drying lotion can sometimes sting a little when i put it on if i tried squeezing a pimple yes i know against the rulesbut it happens but if i use this before bed i will wake up and find that my large red pimples have shrunk significantly overnight  depending on the size of the breakout sometimes it disappears completely within a dayof all of the mb products that i have tried this my favorite acne treatment solutioni believe anyone who has acne prone sensitive skin would find it extremely beneficial  the best way to apply it is to use a clean qtip and dip it through the clear solution and down into the pink powder at the bottom  it is the combination of these two ingredients that will help to clear breakouts  this is a highly recommended product and it definitely is a worthwhile investment and lasts a long time for the price you payusually a bottle lasts me at least  months

review: my saving grace i have used everythingand when i say everything i am talking about home remedies to expensive treatments and products at highend retailersand finally i find what i have been looking for i never even considered that my water could be hard throughout time my hair has always had sheen and shine and was fairly tamable for the past couple of years after an unpleasant salon bleach job my hair changed texture it became dry brittle coarse and just difficult to manage it was a nightmare for me because all of the years it spent being effortless now it had become grueling and dreadful to fix my hair i had even gone to my doctor for thyroid and other hormonal testing because i was sure that something other than the bad salon experience was causing my hair this havoc someone i was complaining to about this had suggested that i may have hard water and to try a hard water shampoo what hard water i have seen the commercials but never really thought about having it andor that it could cause problems with my hair enter this malibu hard water wellness shampoo and conditioner luster life bounce softness non frizzy mane its a miracle it really is i am so happy with this purchase and it has helped to restore my hair almost to the condition i was used to before after one use my hair felt better i cannot rave enough about it because i am so happy that it has helped i will be a lifelong customer and will spread the word to all i know thank you for a great product  if you are a consumer looking for something for dry frizzy unmanageable hairgive this a try it cannot hurt  you may be like me  be amazed at how great your hair will feel afterwards my new favorite shampoo  conditioner

review: ive used other dry shampoo sprays and this one is one of my favorites the scent is soso neither great nor awful but its also not overpowering like some ive used it seems to dissipate quickly it also doesnt go on as thick as some other sprays which makes it easier to brush into the hair without leaving white residue theres sometimes a little white powder but it rubsbrushes in easilythe dry shampoo does absorb oil fairly well and the best part is that it doesnt feel like a ton of hairspray in your hair it feels weightless and doesnt itch or glue my hair like some others and it washes out easily without leaving residue  something ive found with other dry shampoo productsit doesnt seem like it would work for extremely oily hair but it does work well for use between washes i get about one extra day  wash dry shampoo wash on the third day i could maybe stretch it another day but not without also using other products
product: klorane dry shampoo with nettle

review: i love this stuff used it for the first time today  it literally saved my hair it has natural shine again for the first time in a year its soft to touch again  even without my normal detangler its almost completely tangle free due to our horrible hard water in south idaho i was despairing over having to cut all my long fine hair off to control the damage  now i wont have to i couldnt be happier with is product i am already telling friends  fam

review: true to its name this is accurately a very rich body cream  i have chronically dry skin as a result of two rounds of accutane and this cream is perfect for me  what i love about it is that it thoroughly moisturizes but it also absorbs well and doesnt leave the skin feeling greasy or slippery this is a real plus because with a lot of creams i find i have to avoid my hands or wait awhile for them to absorb because they make my hands too greasy to use or can make it hard to immediately put on clothes comfortably  it does seem to be scented and im neutral about the fragrance  it isnt a pungent fragrance though it isnt light either  but it is definitely more noticeable than the dermatologist recommended lotions and creams which have a very subtle almost medicinal smell from whatever they are made with vs an intentional perfumefragrance smell  i cant quite put my finger on what it smells like exactly but it is pretty neutral  it does seem to be subtly feminine but isnt as floraly as other lotions out therein sum this is a great lotion  yes it is more expensive than drugstore varieties but it feels very luxurious going on and does the job

review: my hair is extremely long very fine and sadly starting to thin  its been hard to deal with for as long as i can remember and even though ive been living with it my entire life i never quite became good with hair the way some people do  on its own its neither perfectly straight nor wavy it tends to frizz and it attracts static like nobodys business for the longest time i wore my hair in the same layered style turning the ends under and trying to feather the front  or trying to wear a side part that didnt end up looking greasy by the end of the day  forget flatirons  they make my hair look limp and in need of a good wash and in spite of practicing at it every day for a solid year watching every tutorial out there and getting an inperson demo from my stylist i never learned to make spiral curls with onethe advent of the curling wand was a game changer for me  i dont have to worry about my wrist not wanting to move a certain way and i didnt have to learn any special techniques  its just wrap count and release i can vary the waves by changing the size of the section of hair and i can loosen them just a touch with a slight tug while theyre still warm  the versatility of these appliances is amazing  i love that they come in so many sizes and shapes a allow for so many looksthe sultra bombshell is my fourth curling wand  the   inch straight barrel allows me to do a big subtle wave thats smooth and sleek  i love the morticia addams look i can create with this  the waves are so loose my hair looks like it just has an easy natural wave  my hair is extremely long so a barrel this size works fairly well  im not sure how it would do on shorter hairthe wand only has one heat setting but it heats quickly  i have another high end wand that gets much much hotter which is kind of scary actually so if you have very thick or very coarse hair you might want to experiment a bit to get your section size and time righti would definitely recommend this wand for anyone who has really long fine hair like mine  at the amazon price of  its actually more expensive than the nume wand i have but if it lasts as long as that one has ive had it four years it would be worth iti do have to note that i dont use the heat gloves  i discovered very early on that they get in my way and cause my very fine hair to frizz  i am extremely careful when handing these hot wands however and i dont recommend that anyone go without the glove who hasnt before unless you are using a wand that has a cool tip most higher end wands do not have one but both of my remington wands have this feature  it takes a lot of practice to handle these things safely so its better to practice with a glove or a cool tip beforehand
product: sultra the bombshell rod curling iron

review: if i would have known how good my hair would have looked after using this hair dryer and how fast the drying goes i would have bought this years ago seriously for years i would spend  to  on various hair dryers from department stores thinking theres no way some  hair dryer could work that well then a year would go by it would lose its oompf and id buy another then one day  or so years ago i finally got fed up with the frizz and split ends and asked my hair stylist what brand he would recommend he gave a couple of names one of which was babyliss so off to the interwebs i went and did a lot of comparing and review reading days later i pulled the trigger on the babylisspro omgee why didnt i do this soonerbefore i would have to blow dry my hair straight but it would still be frizzy so id have to use a flat iron the result would be wasted time and lots of split endsnow i use this and have cut my styling time in halfbetter yet since i dont use a flat iron  no split ends i held off on posting a review because when people post right after they get a product it doesnt always speak to its longevity the novelty hasnt worn off and we havent had a chance to discover the products problems okay i admit  i got a little busy but i truly intended to post after owning it for a year well that turned into  years however the dryer is still going strong and works like a champif youre thinking about investing in a hair dryer and taking a step up from your department store purchase then buy this babyliss
product: babylisspro nano titanium dryer

review: ive bought other la rocheposay items in the past and have always really liked them so i was eager to try out this new product  i was expecting it to be heavier than it is but it really does feel like a serum on your skin which is amazing considering that it has such a high spf of it doesnt leave a white cast to the skin at all and it plays nicely with moisturizer and foundation over itwhen buying beauty products i usually check paula begouns beautypedia site to see if the claims that the product makes are valid ones and beautypedia had this to say about this productso why doesnt this earn our highest rating while this serum contains a notable amount of vitamin e tocopherol its disappointing that the other antioxidants are included in such minute concentrations especially given that this is advertised as a highpotent antioxidant complex we wish larocheposay would have included more but well take any we can get since the research is clear that combining antioxidants with sunscreen gives skin a significant environmental boost and helps to further offset the damaging effects of uv light      as far as the claim that youll see improvement in the appearance of dark spots goes dont get your hopes up there this formula lacks the skinlightening ingredients needed to do that but at least the sun protection will help prevent sundamaged induced dark spots from getting worseoverall this is a nice sunscreen but i may stick with mynbspa datahookproductlinklinked classalinknormal  uv clear spf    ozanbspsince the ingredients in the elta md especially the niacinamide are better for getting rid of dark spots

review: i had some awapuhi styling oil which i bought to control frizzies  mostly i loved the scent  hard to describe and fragrance preferences are very personal  so i tried the sea salt spray after reading reviewsif you like the tousled look for short hair this product is nothing short of miraculous  you spray a light mist over your hair  dash your fingers around  and youre done once you pull yourself up off the floor from surprise  its instantly so cool looking and i know nothing about styling my hairnow to temper this review ill tell you that ive since bought some indie sea salt spray the top rated sss on ultas site  indie is waterier and gives far less definition  it leaves your hair kinda drippy  great for taming frizzies  not as great for the beach tousled locksfor me i only slightly prefer the awapuhi sss scent to the indies scent  mitchell couldnt replicate the same awesomeness of the wild ginger quite as well with sss as with his styling oil  but the coconut scent of the indie smells like a salonproduct version of coconut scent  so its a bit of a toss up  but the difference in how easy styling is with awapuhi is remarkablein short best styling product ive ever tried  hands down  its pricier per oz but way worth it

review: at the outset i suggest looking at the numerous videos on youtube or at fhis website search for fhi stylus or fhibrands dot com for pointers on how to use this styling brush  this styling brush does a lot of things well and some things not quite as well  if you are looking for big waves and flattening or controlling small sections of hair this tool is great  if you are looking for a straightener for lots of hair or a curling iron to make tight curls other tools will probably work better  however if you are looking for a single tool that will do just about everything except for small tight curls this tool is the one to getfor big waves and big curls this device is great  the brush is light and the temperature settings are easy to use  the settings are approximate for each type of hair  the easiest way to figure out the temperature to use is to start with a setting lower than you think you need and see how well that temperature works  overheating hair is generally not a good idea and can damage hair so easing into a temperature setting from the low side is better than going past the optimal temperaturethe brush heats up quickly  most of the ceramic areas heater areas have bristles to minimize the chance of burning hands and fingers but the edges of the brush can get warm  i am always careful around heated styling tools though the hottest areas on this brush are difficult to reachuse the brush on a section of hair at a time  the size of the section matters and changes the ultimate effect  experiment with different size sections and different curling techniques wrapping the hair clockwise or counterclockwise wrapping hair around the brush completely vs a sweeping brush stroke etc to see how your hair reacts  also consider using a spray to help hold the curls  you can use this styling brush as a straightener but a dedicated straightener might be simpler to use though the temperature control on this brush is better than many and probably most straightenersthis styling brush has lots of other features including a noslip handle and textured edge areas to help slide through hair  the brush powers off automatically after an hour for safety  the brush comes with a thermal bag to permit transporting an iron shortly after use so you can throw this brush in a suitcase without waiting for it to cool completelyas a single allpurpose styling tool this particular tool does most things well and easily replaces up to three different tools  the tool is light weight and easy to handle  the tool looks good too  though it would be unusual to impress friends with a styling tool it might be possible with this oneenjoy
product: fhi heat stylus thermal styling brush

review: i had previously tried the red sandalwood soap and preshave as well as the green soap and preshave i have used this white variety in conjunction with the green preshave menthol and eucalyptus as well as by itself i found that it loads the shaving brush with lather as quickly as the other proraso soaps which is to say that youll have all the soap you need in the brush within  seconds note that you will have to soak your shaving brush for a few minutes to make this happen i found that blooming the soap was of limited utility as this isnt a hard soap puck but rather more like a stiff creamthe proraso white seems to have a thicker lather than the other varieties it gives very good protection and nice skin feel after rinsing off to me it smells like tea tree oil a somewhat sharp almost citrus smell that is quite subdued and wont negatively interact with any other fragrance you wish to use as an aftershave i have gotten the best performance with using this soap in conjunction with the proraso green preshave i apply the preshave in a small quantity while the brush is soaking just a few minutes then lather the soap directly on top without rinsing you may need to add a bit of water to the suds to get the right consistency as you go but this stuff when properly hydrated is slick all but the most aggressive shaving implements should work well with this stuff i was able to do my first few straight razor shaves without cutting myself with a safety razor and a good blade the stubble comes off almost like magic i was just able to perform my closestever shave with this tactic highly recommendedassociated gear parker  safety razor boker tree brand straight razor escali badger hair brush proraso green preshave

review: i bought this last december  i waited until january to try it because i wasnt sure how my skin would react and didnt want to look strange over the holidays  i started out using it every day  days a week  i did this for  weeks  at first it really stung  but over time my skin became used to it and there was no uncomfortable feeling at all when using iti have very sensitive skin and i was a little afraid of using it to be honest  at first it seemed like it drew out all the imperfections in my skin  in other words it seemed to show every little hill and valley  now i should mention that im  years old and although i thought it would be great to get rid of wrinkles having read other reviews i thought it would be awesome to get rid of some of the acne scars that i hadas the weeks went by i did notice an improvement  heres the thing if you want a fast fix this isnt the device for you  however if you are willing to put in a little effort over a longer period of time get this  its  minutes a day thats not a huge time suck and it worksafter  weeks i stopped using it for a month  thats when i really saw improvement in the healing phase  i noticed that my jowl area looked much tighter as did the wrinkles around my eyes  even the skin on my cheeks was tighter  i did see a marked improvement in my acne scars as well  so after the month off ive been using it twice a week now just to keep things looking good  i may do another round of  days a week in the fall but for now im very pleased with the resultsyes this device is a bit pricey but compared to laser done in a dermatologists office its a bargain  and it works at least it did for me  but again its not going to work if you use it for a weekyou have to commit to the time and  minutes a day is not much time to commit to really
product: tria smooth beauty laser  fda cleared  younger looking skin in as little as  weeks

review: okay i am not understanding where half of these reviews are coming from anybody who claims that it is sticky or is leaving any film on their legs is admitting that they are not rubbing it in the way theyre supposed to if you do not follow the directions how can you expect the results i use the product for literally  days it is said to use it morning and night i only use it in the mornings because i was just trying it out i wanted to see how it would react with my sensitive skin and all of that my experiences are as follows i put a normal amount in my palms about a quarter and rubbed it into my thighs and bum being honest i probably could have rubbed it in longer but like most i dont have all the time in the world so i rubbed it in for about a minute to two minutes on each leg with that being said it was not sticky in the slightest it did not leave any sort of film i truly dont understand how women who dont spend the time to actually rubbing the lotion can then complain that it is sticky or what not i dont know if people know this but there is no way to get rid of cellulite really even with exercise lifestyle change whatever it will not be going away permanently you can improve the appearance temporarily that is what i am aiming to do for the summertime in just the first  days my skin was much firmer it was obviously smoother because i have been applying lotion but it was a nice firm smooth im going to wait closer to the summertime to do my full  weeks but if i had this kind of experience in just  days and applying it half of the recommended time i think it will go well this is not a magic lotion that will make cellulite disappear in  weeks forever a lot of these reviews are of women complaining of stickiness and no results in  weeks lets be honest its pretty obvious that they are not applying it the correct way and not rubbing it in
product: vichy celludestock smoothing body treatment with caffeine  fl oz

review: first of all let me say that proraso is good quality stuff  i gave this  stars because imho it doesnt work as well as the shave creams that come in the tubes  i have a tube of proraso but wanted to try this and the razor glides much better with the cream and i get a much better shave  also from reading all the reviews and tips on how to use this soap a lot of users are saying to swirl the brush directly in the container to start a lather and then transfer to another bowl to complete the lather  i did this and it does work well but that makes it a  process which i dont want to do  id rather squeeze cream out of a tube directly on the brush then do the lather in a shaving bowl  and for those asking if this is a hard puck or a cream its kind of inbetween  its not as hard as a traditional bar of soap but its definitely not a cream  its definitely solid enough that you can take the product out of the bowl and hold it in your hand put it back in the bowl and you wouldnt need to wipe any residue off your hand
product: proraso shaving soap in a bowl sensitive skin  oz

review: i understand many people might have benefit from utilizing this product for their hair loss on their scalp which i initially tried only to be disappointed  i tried using it to advance my hairline a bit by placing the hair fibers in front of my hairline in the temporal region  i then tried using it to fill in my beard as it is a little patchy in some areas  the trouble i had is when applying it i realized it the expensive scientificallyengineered hair fibers seemed comparable to that of a dark brown charcoal powder  my complaint is that the product seemed cheap and did not do a good job for me in advancing my hairline in my temples or filling in my beard  it simply looked like i was rubbing dirt or soot on my face and scalp  the next time i have a barbecue i plan to trial using the powder from the charcoal itself to see if it truly is comparable  if im far out of left field on this one ill edit my review however based on what i had been lead to believe regarding the efficacy of this product and the price i had paid i will not be able to increase my star rating  i dont like to write reviews where i express disappointment but after paying  for this tiny bottle of temporary supposed hair thickening agent i have little recourse else to make  i hope others have been more successful and have enjoyed using this product to its fullest extent but unfortunately that was not the case for me
product: toppik hair building fibers

review: the product is rock hard to the touch and almost impossible to run through your hair im not sure if im using the product incorrectly because there is no clear instruction i tried it on dry hair damp hair wet hair and even fresh out of the shower blow dried hair the product is hard to use and once you finally do get it in your hair and it looks okay okay is all your going to get the product is hard to wash out and doesnt hold well i listened to a youtube with their recommendation of the product and now realize that youtuber was probably paid for the advertisement because this product is not worth the cost at all

review: toleriane teint is indicated for sensitive and combination to oily skin but it also suits my normal to dry sensitive skin well the texture is a thick mousse instead of being thin or runny but it goes on light instead of heavy before applying it i follow my usual skin care routine including applying a good face serum face and eye creams and corrective concealer for dark circles and blemishes i dab small amounts of toleriane teint on my forehead cheekbones nose and neck and spread it with my fingers by using an outward motion until it all blends together this product is so easy to blend and feels good on my skin its not at all greasy and doesnt feel damp or rub off if touched plus i havent experienced any caking it also doesnt accentuate my fine lines like some other foundations this product gives my skin a velvety soft and smooth finish that feels breathable and looks natural and lovely plus its fragrance and preservative free the golden beige is a bit dark for my untanned skin but the tone is a good match and still looks attractive and natural overall im really pleased with this foundation
product: la rocheposay toleriane teint mattifying mousse foundation  fl oz

review: excellent product i was first introduced to these capsules on a cruise when i got a salon facial i bought them and forgot about them for many months i finally tried them at home and loved the fragrance especially the rose and the way the oil absorbed into my skin and made it feel so soft i dont use them twice a day only one capsule at night rotating between the rose and the lavender if i accidentally skip a night i can really notice a difference in the softness of my skin i am on my third jar of capsules and i highly recommend them

review: i bought the eshave verbena lime preshave oil shave cream and this after shave lotion in the hopes of coming out smelling like a lime  well that part works and this post shave lotion adds a nice touch of fragrance moisture for my face and does a nice job getting the red out when my shaving technique causes a bit of irritation on my necki dont feel an immediate relief or soothing sensation when this lotion is applied as i do with some other after shave products but the aforementioned benefits do in my opinion deserve high marks  i also like the light hint of lime as it not only coincides with its preshave and shaving cream cousins but it isnt overbearing which i like  theres nothing i cant stand more than any cosmetic product leaving a strong scent that stays on you all day until you can shower it offthis is nice stuff and should you try it im sure youll be happy with it

review: the color is darker than we expected based only on the image provided on amazon  however the narrow width and long thin tube is easier to control for us than traditional short thicker tubes  particularly for thinner lips this lipstick can be a much better way to apply lipstick than lipstick in a traditional tubethe lipstick applies easily and smoothly  as noted above with the thinner barrel it is easier to control application so the smooth application helps control even morethe finish is a bit more matte than we anticipated  if more shine is desired try applying a light layer of lip balm over the top of the lipstick  on the other hand in a bright environment the finish should be less reflective which can be desirable for many reasonsgenerally we like this lipstick  the ease of control for smaller hands the smooth application and the bright color are all positive features  the only issue we have is the price which we consider a bit high for lipstick  however the price is somewhat consistent with other highend lipsticks and though we are always amazed at the prices of highend makeup this lipstick seems to work a bit better and last longer than discount store lipstick  does this lipstick work so much better than discount store lipstick that it is worth two or three times the price of discount store lipstick  for us the price is too high to buy this lipstick for routine use but it may be a great lipstick for a gift and for special occasionsenjoy
product: vincent longo thinstick lipstick

review: okay so i first used this product as part of a ginger kit it came in that i got as a gift from my hair stylist  i have long thick wavy but very poofy and frizzy coarse hair  i have used other salon oils and they were always super expensive and left my hair oily or made my blowout not last as long because my hair got oily faster  not this one  but it was pricey so instead of repurchasing it i went to the drug store and tried to buy a cheaper oil as a replacement  huge mistake  this oil is far superior to anything you can buy in the drug store  why  because it reduces drying time and frizz better than any other product i have used without weighing my hair down or making it look greasy  it makes such a dramatic difference when trying to achieve a salon comparable blowout at home yourself  i would recommend this product to anyone regardless of hair type  the only recommendation i would make is to place it on your ends first as they tell you to and then use the residue left on your hands for the top of your hair  best oil i have ever used
product: awapuhi wild ginger styling treatment oil

review: ive been using this for a while now and love it my skin feels like silk after my shower now i want to comment on the leakage ive purchased this directly from sabon as well and its the same way from them the oil in the product is thin and some will get past the lid in shipping the jar will be oily when it arrives it will appear that its not full but i think thats because the scrub settles at the bottom and the oil remains on top ive never had any completely spilled as some others have reported i would return it right away if that were the casewhen i purchased from amazon it was wrapped the same as when i purchased directly from sabon online in  layers first layer was the original sabon wrapping it still had the sticker from sabon this layer will have the most oil on it the second layer was a sort of baggie and had no oil on the outside the third layer was tightly wrapped bubblewrap which covered the entire container quite well my method to unpack is to remove the first  layers then sit the container still in its original wrapping on a towel or paper towel to catch the outer oil i usually do this at my bathroom sink i remove the original wrapper then sit the entire container under some hot running water to remove the outer oil using a towel i dry the container it will still be slippery im not sure this can be avoided i then us a towel to remove the lidi keep a pair of unused lol carryout chopsticks in the shower dont break them apart the thick end is perfect for stirring the oil into the scrub it also makes a great scoop to retrieve small amounts without dropping any of that precious scrubas for the scent ive only ever used the mango kiwi i love it so much i really need to try another but its hard to switch when you know what you like another bonus ive noticed is that my bathroom will smell like this scrub for a couple days after ive used it no complaints herei hope this review is helpful
product: sabon body scrub

review: if i could have only one nail product it would be opi nail envy when i finally purchased it at my local sally beauty store i was beyond skeptical  felt like i was surely throwing my  away by my standards i thought that nearly  for  ounces of polish is exorbitant unlike everything else ive tried however it really works  i noticed a difference within a weeks use im so glad the many positive reviews here convinced me to give nail envy a try my only complaint is that i didnt find it soonerthis is the   only product in  years of spending money on various nail hardeners strengtheners oils cuticle creams oils dietary chages  oral supplements that has made any difference whatsoever for my chronically weak splitting nubby nails cuticle overgrowth  cracking has greatly lessened polish stays on longer due to less severe nail flexing  bending which used to cause my polish to start chipping off within hours i finally have nails i love instead of sadlooking ragged  embarrassing nails no opi or sally affiliation just an amazed  happy customer
