review: im a woman in my  who has switched to shave soaps  a brush after years of canned foam the proraso green soapcroap is my favorite and the white is very similar both are more of a croap cross between hard cream  soap rather than a straight up hard puck of soap it lathers crazy easily with a wet badger or boar brush  the marco method if youre new to wet shaving or having trouble making lather google it  you wont regret it and provides a good close irritationfree shave i lather in the plastic proraso bowl directly on the soap then go straight to leg i have also done a separate bowl lather with this and it worked nicely after use i leave the lid off for a couple of hours to let the soap dry somewhat i shave in the shower  store my soap there so theres a lot of water and then store it with the lid on the white has a slight menthol feel but considerably less than the green in my opinion the white has a light scent of roses  fresh cut grass its very light and clean and i think it could be considered the most feminine between the green red  white proraso soaps i had issues with irritation from the red proraso disappointing since i loved the scent but neither the green or the white cause any problems for me overall i am extremely pleased with this soap and it will definitely be in my regular rotation

review: it is very easy to make curls with this flat iron i am not a hair stylist and ive never been able to master that technique mainly because im too afraid i barley turned my wrist to bend the hair at the ends and was surprised that i made curls  if you only want to bend the hair only turn your wrist at the ends i was also surprised at how tight the curls were because the iron is   and my hair is only shoulder length the outside does get hot and you can use it as a wand curler also i havent tried this the hot exterior did not interfere with me straightening my hair it was perfectly comfortable to hold at the bottom and with the silicone tips but i did burn myself putting it away i will have to remember it came with a pair of gloves another thing that i liked is that the plates wrap around the edges of the flatiron i was able to get very close to the roots it made my hair very shinycons you only have the option of the  preset temperatures     and  i would preferred a sliding scale or even better a digital reading also there is no indication that it has reached the temperature which i guess isnt a big deal since it says it heats up in less than a minute the outside takes longer but my ghd platinum makes a noise and it heats up in like  sec i wasnt willing to knock off a star for these thingsanother random thing that i like is that it has a regular plug not a bulky plug with the reset button

review: i was looking for some glitter to apply to my eyelids for very special occasions and found this i loooove the color and received sooooooo many wonderful comments the trickiest part is the application its highly and strongly recommended to hold a piece of mail or put scotch tape with a paper towel sheet under the bottom lid or the glitter will no matter what you do stick to your face where you dont want it to make a neat and clean outter line where you want the glitter to stop apply a strip of scotch tape to the outter part of the eye meaning apply the tape at an angle from the bottom lids to the outter edge of your eyebrows to apply the glitter you must use some false eyelash or elmers glue and either a makeup brush a qtip or your finger and dab if you try to swipe the glitter on it will make a mess on your lids by globbing together and taking off some of the glue that was applied to remove the glue and glitter it rather simple you can peel it away it doesnt hurt at all yes some may be left behind you can take a qtip to remove the rest or you just use some soap and water and rub away its also highly and strongly recommended to put something underneath the glitter canister so the glitter doesnt get everywhere when dipping the brush qtip or your finger and shaking some excess off or it just falls off upon applying either way it makes a mess but looks gorgeous when its done

review: through bzzagent i was able to get this product in a discounted price however my opinion is honest and unbiasedi thought that if you want to buy this product you are probably thinking about buying this or clarisonic well i have used both so i thought i will do a little comparisoni have been really enjoying my luna mini i had a clarisonic mia before i felt that it cleaned my skin a lot better than only with my hands it felt harsh on my skin though i had never thought that i had a sensitive skin until i started using my mia even though i used the most gentle brush delicate my skin would just feel irritated after using itthis luna mini is so gentle on my skin i had to get used to the feeling of the silicone bristles but i like it i like that my skin doesnt feel irritated after using it i also like that this has two speed i would use the higher speed all over my face except my delicate eye area where i use the more gentle speedanother feature that i enjoy is that it pulses and tells you when to move from one area to another this is something that clarisonic mia doesnt havethis is something that didnt bother me with mia but i had to charge it around every  weeks i have been using luna mini for a month and hasnt had to charge it again since the first charge it says that luna mini can go to  uses with one charge so if you use it twice a day thats like  days or  monthscomparing between luna mini and clarisonic mia in my opinion luna mini is the winner i love that its more gentle on my skin cleanses just as well and cheaper in the long run because i dont need to buy a new brush every  monthsi hope this review can help you

review: this lip balm is an excellent product i received it in my ipsy glam bag and fell in love with it i used it on my chapped lips and it nourished my lips enough to reduce the severity of the chapped areas it also helped them to hurt less although i think that was just a side effect of the moisturizing agent the lip balm is smooth and not greasy or thick it also lasts a long time that i like because i am not a fan of needing to reapply a product frequently i would apply some in the morning and continued to have moisturized lips for the majority of the day unless i atewiped it off somehow a little bit goes a long way so i was able to use this product for a long while before running out i was afraid that i wouldnt like the flavor but i didnt mind it and i grew to like it i would recommend this product to anyone looking for a lightweight lip balm it is especially useful during the winter months

review: ive had this for awhile and ive used about half of it i dont use it as a cleanser alone usually but its very good for taking off makeup and for double cleansing i do notice that while using this product my skin is nicer my pores are smaller and my skin is less oily i usually use it either at night before i wash my face or in the morning alone i sometimes also even use it as a toner it has a very nice scent and it is pricey but the size is very largei like this product because its versatile i use it with a cotton pad and it makes my face feel really fresh and clean i would consider buying this again when i am finished because i spent awhile without it and realized i wish i brought it with me because it did make a difference in my skin routine however if youre looking for a new cleanser alone i dont think this is the product i have very sensitive skin and this never made me break out at all or have any sort of reaction i also have combination skin and it doesnt affect my dry spots and sometimes even moisturizes them more

review: i have really nice skin its one of the things i admire and pride myself about my body one day during finals week im guessing excessive stress made this happen but i got a pimple it hurt so bad and was huge when i do rarely get a pimple you can barely see them because i treat them before and during its early emergence on my face somehow i came across please dont publicly shame me when i say this an instagram post on yahoo of a kylie jenner snapchat of how she treats her face for acne due to that snapchat and my desperation i forked over  on this drying lotion why did i do that this stuff just chemically burns the crap out of my face left the area peeling and left behind a dark case of hyperpigmentation my skin isnt even that sensitive never again will i buy something like this to put on my face ill stick to the basics that have always worked for meheres what works for me if youre curious i get almost all of this stuff on amazona gentle cleanser cetaphil or neutrogenaoil cleansing every now and then olive oil and castor oil with a few drops of trader joes tea tree oil are my favesacv mixed with water as a toner or burts bees tomato tonertea tree oil and clean and clears persagel  to treat bumps and pimples ive learned that if you really want to have nice skin you have to protect it and keep it moisturized also keep your routine simpleolay total effects  in one spf  or olay complete for combinationoily skin spf  in the am depends on the seasonolay regenerist night cream in the pm or sr luna oil with sr good genes serumthe only nondrug store things i use on my face are sunday rileys luna oil and good genes serum theyre pretty darn good the luna oil also has certain antiseptic properties that help prevent acne crazy right it also makes my skin so soft the serum is good for hyperpigmentation and brightening skin both of them do many other things too sephora has a duo kit for  it was a birthday gift to myself i work on campus dont judge as a college student i often times dont get as much sleep that im suppose to and i was afraid that it would start showing in my face even though the saying is black dont crack i got this duo to help prevent premature aging wrinkles bags crowsfeet saynotofillers saynotobotox agegraciouslyside note i use to have really bad oily skin in early high school i would dry it out with acne astringents and skip out on moisturizer at night because i didnt want my face to be really oily eventually i realized that my face was overproducing oils because of this behavior the moment i started using gentle cleansers oils and moisturizers the moment my skin realized it didnt need to drown itself in sebum as i go through my day i still do produce oil on my skin but its not excessive its just a healthy amount to protect my face from the harsh environment and create a healthy glow during the warmer months i walk around with a pack of oil blotting sheets just in casei hope this helped someone i know it was a lot to read also use smileamazoncom to make your purchases anytime you buy something amazon will make a donation to a charity of your choice im donating to the leukemia and lymphoma society

review: i know theres a movement away from high lather shampoos  and believe me i tried wen and loreacuteals evercreme like everyone else in hopes of some miracle for my baby fine hair but conditioning cleansers just weighed my hair down making it look limp and greasy  so i need to start by saying im thrilled with the superrich almost puddinglike lather you get from color wow security shampoo  ive been using it for two weeks in conjunction with the color wow conditioner which i absolutely adore and so far am pleased with the resultsthe big distinction between the two is that the shampoos fragrance is much milder and more pleasant than the conditioner which smells a bit chemically  however of the two products i think the conditioner provides more tangible results  thats not to say that the shampoo isnt top notch  i love the rich lather and the shine it gives my hair  i just wish it was specially formulated for fine hair like the conditioner because since using the shampoo ive noticed that my hair starts to droop by days end  also the price is fairly prohibitive  the cost of the two together is  and while a little really does go a long way thats just too expensive for every day useall in all an exceptional haircare line if you can afford it

review: you simply cant go wrong with tan towels some info on the products  the classic formula will only knock the glow off the white of your skin if you get kind of boo radley looking like i do so you may be happier with the plus formula if you like a little more color you will probably have to apply the classic  or  times to get a good tan color and depending on your preference the same can go for the plus not jersey shore tan just a nice healthy i spent the weekend in fiji glow either way tan towel makes an excellent productsome tips for application first enlist a partner if you can if youre going to do your entire body youll need help reaching the middle of your back for instance you may wish to start at your face and work your way down to your feet or vice versa i personally do my face  neck first then feet legs derriere stomach and chest at that point i wash my hands thoroughly and let my husband get whatever areas i didnt whether working alone or with a helper the key is to keep moving with that towel and blend the big areas where you stopped previously into the ones you just worked on eg blend upper arms into chest the tan towels dry quickly so you will be able to get dressed within  minutes depending on your preferencebiggest thing to remember do not use any lotions makeup or get your skin wet until your color has fully developed   hours possibly more of course as with all selftanners make sure you exfoliate and do any necessary hair removal before you begin application soon youll be a pro at it and will love having a nice healthy glow thats not damaging your skin

review: im officially a fan of juice all natural skin oroducts  ive been using the daily moisturizer the blemish peel and the sensitive skin peel for several weeks now and my fair sensitive breaks out over everything skin looks outstanding  ive gotten  comments a day in the last few weeks about how radiant i look  really does something for the selfesteem for us women of a certain age to hear thatthis kit includes an age defy serum which goes on like a light gel and is worn under your moisturizer  i have noticed in the last two weeks my skin has felt really dry and tight this has made a big difference  i wish they made all over body serum like thisi think this would make a great gift for someone who would appreciate a higher end skin product but i took off one star because the sizes you get with this are small sample size not full size and i think that they are priced too high for it to be a good deal  id pay  for this and feel like i was giving a very nice gift without breaking the bank

review: why does anyone buy a votive candle  for ambiance style and scent right  this votive comes prettily wrapped in tissue paper and is contained within its own decorative cardboard box  the box and the glass candle have a small coinlike token wrapped around the middle its medium sized  its almost as tall as my  is long shorter only by about a  inch  its a little bit wider than the   since this is a soy candle it will and does burn for a really long time  they claim  hours  ive not measured it but i dont doubt that it burns that long  the wicks are of high quality no smoking or popping like you see from cheaper candles  the scent is strong and just this one votive can scent a large room  i burn one in my open living and kitchen  area  and it is quite pleasing  as for the scents i like woodsy vanilla sandalwood types and bergamot tobacco is one of my favorites  ive been buying these candles for several years now and am glad to see them on amazon since theyre pretty hard to find in my town  scent is a personal thing but i can assure you that youll be happy with the quality
product: archipelago bergamot tobacco signature boxed candle

review: i have three other merkurs a  and two  classics closed bar and open comb this by far blows them all out of the water i have a few aggressive vintage razors that are single edge as well as the classic gillette red tip and i find this one give me the closest shave with the least amount of irritation the razor really sings so you hear it cutting whiskers now i have a thick stubble so i used it with astra sp blades and used arko shave soap and got a wonderful close shave this is not a forgiving razor and i do not recommend it for someone new to the wet shaving game the merkur  or the edwin jaggermuhle  are good razors for that but if you need to move on to a razor that really mows down the stubble then this along with the muhle  should be on your shortlist

review: i received this liquid eye liner today and tried it out immediately i was expecting the tip to feel more like the paint brush types but it is very similar to a fine tip felt marker and draws like one too it is very wet and up close you can see a little bit of watery separation from the black liquid so i just had to go over those areas again on my eyelidsi am happy with the saturation and it leaves a very dark and waterproof liner when dry it is hard to apply if youre new at it like me even though i have a very steady hand and paint in a perfectionist sort of way i still got a bit shaky considering this liner pen is very skinny and short im sure i will find an easier way to keep it steady over time and practicei did notice that this liner will bleed into fine lines and creases on your eye so apply lightly in those areas and allow it to dry if it didnt bleed like that then i would have rated this liner  stars

review: i have used neutrogena eye makeup remover for many years  i use it on my eyes and face neuteogena still has the cheapest price  if you want to upgrade vichy is as good as department store brands like lancme and costs about the same or less on amazonvichy make up remover does its job a lot of makeup came off on the cotton page i used to wipe the makeup remover on my face it has a creamy consistency  this makeup remover hydrates and is gentle on your face  even though neutrogena works well to remove makeup and is the cheapest it doesnt have the extra soothing ingredients like this one  i use other products to hydrate my under eye area but using a makeup remover like vichy means i have more products working together to help my face  hydration is especially important in winter  due to my budget im going to switch back and forth between the neutrogena and this vichy eye make up remover i recommend both depending on your needs i say paying more for this one is worth it if you want a remover that will be the most gentle and hydrating

review: this is the best moisturizer ive ever used  i have extremely oily and acne prone skin  even using oil free moisturizers pose a problem for me  i was hesitant to purchase this moisturizer due to the small quantity and high price im a frugal individual and dont like to pay a lot for my beauty products  however i was desperate to find something because i was tired of having an oily sheen on my skin just a couple of hours after applying my makeup  after a lot of research and reading reviews i decided to take a chance on la roche posay effaclar mat moisturizer  this is by far the best moisturizer ive ever used  dont be put off by how little you get  honestly you only need a small pea sized amount for your entire face  remember this is a mattifying moisturizer  this is meant for oily skin to just keep your skin hydrated and healthy while keeping oil at bay  even after application my skin still feels dry but hydrated  this is a must if you have oily skin like me  if you have normal to dry skin this likely is not for you  ive used this moisturizer for a couple months now and even using it alone without make up i notice a difference in oil build up  there really isnt any ive been using this in conjunction with becca ever matte poreless priming perfector and im so pleased with the results  i do have to blot my skin about mid day but that is a dramatic decrease from having to blot at least  times a day with my previous regimen well worth the money and i will definitely be a repeat customer

review: i have the big quasar md model not the baby quasar i didnt buy my quasar from amazon i bought it from another site but i wanted to share my experience with this so far like everyone before me i was skeptical if it works and just like everyone else i suffer from adult acne tried every cream cleanser and toner out in the marketi have had my quasar md for almost  weeks now and i am slowly seeing results keyword slowly this is not an overnight thing that you will see results right away i think this is why some get discouraged about this light you have to make the time to do it i do it when im laying in bed watching television and you have to do it for their recommended time  minutes so sit or lay down and watch your favorite tv show while you do it and time will fly byplease make sure that your face is clean before you do it and after you use it make sure you also wipe the lens of the quasar after use you dont want all the bacteria from your session to remain on that lens this is so important i wipe my down with alcohol pads from workthe results so far is that my breakouts are less and my skin feels softer and smoother the test was really before my period where i break out the most and it was not that bad i only had one major pimple but the light also helped with it by drying it upso remember it is a slow process that takes patience time and effort on your part if you are looking for quick results this is not for you

review: it is now more than two years after my review below and i am still using the product daily and am still very satisfied  no reason to try anything elsemy first review but after reading others for this product i felt compelled  i am late  and fortunate to have thick hair except for very noticable thinning in the back  about  in diameter  but even this i didnt like  i tried several products without success  those with drugs caused a skin reaction for me  then the person who does my hair suggested i try toppik and gave me suggestions for use  after shampoo dry or allow to dry completely  then put light cost of hairspray on the thin area  apply the toppik immediately to the thin area until it no longer looks thin  then apply a medium coat of hairspray  after the hairspray is completely dry   minutes i brush the area to get rid of the hard feel and look  it looks totally normal  ive had my wife and several others look closely and no one can tell that it is anything other than normal hair  during the day i brush my hair as needed and treat the covered area the same as the rest with no negative effect  even vigorous brushing does not seem to remove the toppik  or at least not enough to notice the toppik is clearly sticking to the thin hair that i have in the area and not just to my scalp  none comes off on the pillow and the next morning it still looks finemy impression from the reviews is that if hair loss is major it may not work nearly as well  it stick well to thin hair and looks normal but directly to the scalp may be very different

review: i can see where people think this is an eye treatment and i guess it is a bit this is way more of a concealer its pigmented and has some pearlized material to deflect light and get rid of the appearance of dark circles although la rocheposay as a company has the reputation for a strong science component to their products they are also a cosmetic company and thats pretty much what this product is  a cosmeticit does contain caffeine which has a diuretic effect to relieve puffiness it also boasts something called pheresorcinol which i guess is their own proprietary compound resorcinol itself is an ingredient in argan oil the company states that its own blend is known for its targeted action on melanin making it sound like this is some kind of skin whitener  all products that claim brightening qualities are really talking about lighteningpuffiness can cast a shadow which can cause the appearance of dark circles this particular product has a metal applicator i gather the point of that in using it to spread the concealer around is that the cold metal will make the puffiness go away you can get the same effect by putting a metal teaspoon in the fridge or in a glass of ice water then using the back of the spoon to press down the puffiness also watch salt intake which causes water retention and adds to the puffinessyou might think caffeine would work on dark circles but that would depend upon the cause of the circles some are hereditary others can be lifestyle related tiredness or can come from age if your circles have a brownish tinge use an apricot colored pigment to counter it this can be in a concealer or just put on the skin then use a concealer if your circles have a blue cast try a yellowish concealerthis particular product is fine as a concealer but make no mistake this is much less of a treatment than it is a cosmetic to hide not cure dark circles short of surgery and injections nothing permanently gets rid of dark circles but a good concealer and knowing how to use it isnt a bad second choice
product: la rocheposay pigmentclar dark circles eye cream  fl oz

review: this mask is excellent  its a great treatment for my dry color treated highlighted hair  i also heat style regularly so dryness is always an issue  its the perfect remedy for my chemically abused dry tresses  i shampoo with a sulfate free formula and then apply a generous amount of this mask making sure my hair is totally saturated especially the midlengths and ends  i then use a heat cap for about  minutes which helps the mask soak into the cuticle as it is opened by the heat  ive also used this mask overnight with good results  because this mask is quite heavy i then rinse for a full five minutes  i apply my regular serum and styling products and let my hair air dry overnight  in the morning i use a curling iron to create loose waves  truthfully after using this mask my hair looks awesome  the ends are smooth and sleek and theres no trace of the crunchy dryness i had prior to using this mask  it truly hydrates incredibly well  in fact i dont think ive ever used a mask that was quite as good as this one  my hair has body and shine and it responds really well to my styling efforts  this mask smells divine and is thick and rich so a little goes a long way so this jar will last a long time even though the recommended usage is once a week  if you dont have a heat cap you can cover your hair with a plastic shower cap and use a hair dryer for about  minutes on low to generate steam which will open the cuticle so the mask can penetrate the hair shaft  you can also use a hot towel microwave a damp towel for  minutes and then carefully wrap it around your hair  when the towel cools repeat this procedure  these two methods work just as well as a heat cap  however this mask works equally well when used overnight just be sure you cover your pillow with a towel  the macadamia oil in this formula obviously has a healing effect which makes it great for dry damaged locks  as long as you rinse well i think this mask would also be suitable for fine hair  all in all i like everything about this mask  it makes my hair look incredible and the effects really last  im a loyal once a week user of this formula and i highly recommend it especially for those who have chemically treated hair  its a superb formula that works great for me and im sure it would work equally well for you
product: macadamia professional nourishing moisture masque

review: ive had this nail strengthener for about  months time and yes  the reviews are correct it really is a superb nail product my nails were really strung out after having gelcoated nails for the past  years or so did not have time for monthly nailtechnician visits so grew my gelcovered nails out and started using nail envy my nails more sturdy than ever even when i accidentally bump my hand somewhere my nails stay intact whereas before using nail envy  they were sure to break chip tearthis is how i used it put  coats on clean nails one coat daily for  days removed everything on day  rubbed olive oil on my nailscuticles on day repeated the cycle for a second weeknow i use it as a top coat

review: ive tried all kinds of stuff and nothing ever seemed to make much of a dent in my bacne but this has cleared everything up by about  its not  but ill take what i can getthe first week it didnt seem to do much i was using  and it seemed to stop any new breakouts from forming but it was hard to tell that early the second week i upped it to  and noticed a much larger improvement its been about a month now and my back is much improved  there are still a few pumps and some slight pinkness that you can see up close but thats it i bought the  size as a tester amount since the regular size seemed kinda pricey im about halfway through the  bottle nowit does smell like rubbing alchohol however so what i do is spray spray spray while holding my breath then take a couple steps away before inhaling again the smell dissipates really quickly fortunately

review: i probably have more dermablend cosmetics than i have of any other one kind so i feel like i am very familiar with their products  this product is finedoes all the things its supposed to  however it came all broken  that is why the  instead of  stars although i realize that is not the manufacturers fault and could have been the mailmansthe product covers everythingat least on my body i havent tried it on other things  i am no longer a teenager and my skin can now produce a bruise when the cat paws my arm where at one time i could walk away from a soccer fight and never showed i participated and i look upon those bruises as evidence i am old  dermablend products are really great to cover up these unsightly spots  this powder foundation is one of their products that i dont use firsti use this lightly after i have done everything else im going to do to my face  it seems to hold my makeup better than anything else ive tried and believe me ive tried plentyif youve never tried dermablend just give one of their products a chance and particularly try them if you have something on your skin anywhere youd like to hide  theres a good chance youll be glad you did

review: i was looking for an organic makeup and discovered this brand i bought this makeup and the green apple age defykit i love this bbcc cream it seems a little like half way between these two types of makeup it does have zinc in it for sunscreen so it does have a bit of lightening to it i am very fair with pink undertones and a lot if creams or makeup are too yellow or too orange for me the light shade blends perfectlyi use juice beauty green apple serum under this plus i use benefit erase paste for my dark eye circles and a couple of dark freckles that i dont like then after serum and the concealer  i put this on i use a pea size squeezed out for my forehead and cheeks and another drop for my jaws and blending to my neck its a bit hard to squeeze out but its very nice and sanitary in the tube i liked it so much after  weeks that i ordered a second tube for my purse i estimate that one tube will last  weeks with the application i described it is a dewy finish but not sticky its hot and humid here in tx and so i use juice loose finishing powder to top it off with a light dusting  if i want or need extra coverage for going to some place special then i skip the juice powder and use bare minerals powder foundation fairly light is my color and it goes well over this juice makeup i love the natural sunscreen as it doesnt make my eyes tear up like almost every sunscreen including clinique does to me this product is easy to use easy to touch up during the day and i love it my daughter is  and tried it one time and wanted her own after wearing mine all weekend she is fair but has a light tan and it makes her face glow but also makes it a tiny bit lighter so she adds bare minerals tinted mineral veil which she uses anyway she says this compares to her clinique cc cream but is not as heavy coverage as the clinique so if you need heavy coverage you can use clinique cc cream or you can use a concealer for trouble areas and use this lovely organic makeup by the way we both think the mild scent is very nice but it fades quickly so you forget it in a few minutes i love the improved moisture and texture of my skin after using this for over a month its really worth a try if you want a more natural make up brand
product: juice beauty stem cellular cc cream   fl oz

review: i received this as a birthday present from my daughter  it proved to be a gateway drug to a more relaxing contemplative morning ritual and entry into the dark world of traditional wet shavingat first i would put a dollop of the cream in my hands and work it into my face with like i would with a shaving gel  this was a nice experience  the eucalyptus and menthol are very soothing and did a very nice job preparing my face for a shaveabout two months after the initial gift i purchased a shaving brush  this one to be precise the brush completely unlocked the potential of the cream  utilizing a face lathering tactic i was able to build a very nice and satisfying lather onto my facei strongly recommend this product but beware it may result in razor acquisition disorder

review: i use this to set and refresh my make up ive never used a setting product before but this was recommend in another review so i thought id try it i was somewhat skeptical since the ingredients all seem so normal in this day and age of every product needing some fancy new buzzword exotic ingredient or new innovative chemical i figured id try it but didnt expect much since most of the aforementioned woweezowy miracle buzzword products which this isnt give me underwhelming results but ive been really surprised what a difference this product makes and the smell is really nicei have breakout prone skin and ive had no breakouts since using this product and if anything my skins been much easier to deal with i dont know if that has anything to do with using this or not but at the very least i can say its definitely not breaking me out or anything but because of my skin i usually have to put my foundation on thick and also try to camouflage some decentsized areas of my face since my breakouts tend to cluster anyone in the same boat knows that its really hard to do without creating a patchy uneven look and a heavy coating that looks nothing like tge texture of skin i feel like this spray does a great job of adding a more natural finish to my makeup as well as smoothing outblending inhiding the areas which before definitely looked like i was trying to hide something ill definitely keep using this product plus its nice to find something effective thats going to last a long time and which i dont have to save up for to afford

review: this palette is totally giftable it comes in an attractive box and then inside there are four separate minipalettesthe key to this is the free travel compact what you are supposed to do is use the pick tool to move the makeup you want for that day to the compact its a great idea and one that should appeal to most peoplemakeup qualitymichelle phan made her debut on youtube where she became a sensation with tween teens and  somethings and okay with moms like me i watched the vids with my thentweennowteen daughter they are truly entertaining and educational i love michelles approach to makeup and life its just a lot more healthy and upbeat than most of the other media influences that my daughter and her friends run acrossin any case michelle caught the eye of a makeup company and they gave her a line the makeup is okay about on par with the sort your buy at the grocery story or the drugstore it is however at a more premium price and you are paying for the namesummaryi think the main problem with this product are the perky colors and the less than optimal pigmentation  lots of comments on this  to which id say how pigmented do you want your turquoise eye shadow to be  these are colors in my opinion geared to very young users  if i saw them on a woman in the workplace id expect her to be reliving the   but thats just me i have old references this makeup though is perfect for girls like my daughter who is  teens like her tend to overdo their makeup the less drastic pigmentation that others are complaining about is exactly what i want my teen using less is moreso excellent gift if the price isnt a problem this collection looks nice and theres a variety of shades to play with do get the free compact and do purchase a selection of brushes the one that came with this is totally pathetic

review: im so torn first time i bought loccitane bar soap i got the verbena scent because it is lemonlemongrass and i absolutely love the scent of that one and then i saw milk milk a soap whose scent is named milk i had to buy it just to find out what it was it came in the mail and i almost wanted to cry milk apparently smells like baby powder straight up baby powder you know the scent im talking about i was so disappointed but at least i knew id enjoy the soap so i hopped in the shower and tried it first let me say loccitane soap might be pricey but you get a ton of soap the bar is huge you could probably cut it into  pieces and each piece would be the amount of a normal bar of soap i actually dont like how large the bar soap is and i cant be bothered to cut it into sections  but it is what it is its not just like youre getting one bar of soap for the price tag youre getting quite a lot of soap it helps justify it also their bar soap is top notch i mean bar soap can only do so much but this is about as good as youll get with bar soap the soap lasts quite a while too size aside leaves my skin feeling nice i wish it were a bit more moisturizing but what bar soap isnt a bit drying not that this is drying but you get my point but the scent when i was in the shower i almost started liking the scent it reminds me of the cologne dior sauvage sauvage has that baby powder scent to it just like this soap i hated that cologne at first but it grew on me and im starting to think this soap is doing the same thing sauvage definitely smells better than the soap but im hoping in time i can grow to appreciate the baby powder scent i wouldnt purchase it again id recommend verbena if youre interested in trying one of these i have not tried lavender but im not a fan of lavender scentslong story short if youre wondering what milk smells like loccitane apparently thinks it smells like baby powder because thats the scent you geton the plus side it isnt a super intense fragrance and mostly goes away after you finish showering and dry off
product: loccitane extragentle vegetable based soap enriched with shea butter

review: this absolutely will lighten scars  i break out often and end up scarring especially in the summer because i tan regularly which makes scars darker  the only thing is if youre covering more than a qtip size area where more product will be able to sit on the skin you have to be prepared to look a lot worse before things get a lot better  it can create something similar to a chemical burn and you have to be ready for it to first be very red then scab over and it requires you to put on neosporin as often as possible certainly every night with a bandaid in order for it to heal properly and not make the situation worse  once it heals you will absolutely without a doubt see a difference  ive tried several products to help with scarring typically with retina and none of them have worked  this worked within about  days but again about  of those were healing time some neosporin to soften the spot up and a little makeup covered it pretty well though  its absolutely worth the work and feeling a little selfconscious for a few days while you heal

review: avobenzoneavobenzone is a primary agent in commercial sunscreens due to its effectiveness in absorbing a wide range of ultraviolet uv rays specifically the type that is known to cause sunburn its been considered a relatively safe chemical but recent research suggests otherwise avobenzone degrades in the sun resulting in the release of free radicals that may actually increase the risk for cancer

review: this matrix detangling solution works quite well better than what i was using before and better than id expected i had been using matrix biolage fortetherapie strengthening conditioner that get good results even with long hair like mine i expect this  bottle will last a long time using only the amount you really needall my other conditioners have been very creamy liquids this is not its almost a paste with about the consistency vaseline would have is squeezed out of a tube a little blob the size of maybe a nickel and rubbed between my hands to spread it out before applying to my wet hair was just rightin the shower i worked it through my wet hair and combed it out while rinsing the results were better than id hoped and saved me minutes and gallons of water id otherwise have used fighting tanglesother things i like about this detangling solution include almost no scent i hate strong scents in my products and that my hair looks nice and is still quite manageable after air dryingin conclusion i was concerned about matrix retiring the strengthening conditioner id come to like a lot this detangling solution seems to replace the conditioning of the old stuff just as well plus gives me much quicker and easier combout of my hair in the shower in fact better than i had expected which earns  stars from meupdate oct  im into my  month of use and im not quite as excited as i was on the first couple of uses it worked great then but hair like so many things varies from wash to wash with respect to tangles i still have some occasions where im fighting stubborn tangles in the shower this isnt  but it is an improvement over my previous conditioner just not as much as i first thoughti still think its worth  stars and is very good but isnt quite the ultimate solution to shampoo tangles i was hoping it might be

review: im a woman in my  who has switched to shave soaps  a brush after years of canned foam the proraso green soapcroap is my favorite and the white is very similar both are more of a croap cross between hard cream  soap rather than a straight up hard puck of soap it lathers crazy easily with a wet badger or boar brush  the marco method if youre new to wet shaving or having trouble making lather google it  you wont regret it and provides a good close irritationfree shave i lather in the plastic proraso bowl directly on the soap then go straight to leg i have also done a separate bowl lather with this and it worked nicely after use i leave the lid off for a couple of hours to let the soap dry somewhat i shave in the shower  store my soap there so theres a lot of water and then store it with the lid on the white has a slight menthol feel but considerably less than the green in my opinion the white has a light scent of roses  fresh cut grass its very light and clean and i think it could be considered the most feminine between the green red  white proraso soaps i had issues with irritation from the red proraso disappointing since i loved the scent but neither the green or the white cause any problems for me overall i am extremely pleased with this soap and it will definitely be in my regular rotation

review: i already had a vintage safety razor from gillette and loved it but the handle was a little short so i opted for this one based on the reviews and that it was discounted with prime i like the look feel and shave i had with it the only thing that was a little awkward is that rather then spin the base to open the blade protection you have to actually screw the head off to open it up and swap out blades im hoping that the constant motion of unscrewingreplacing the razor head wont eventually lead to dullingstripping of the screw or receiver additionally you have to be conscious of how youre holding the head when you screw it back on otherwise your fingers are on the blades again im used to a really old gillette that has a dial on the bottom to open the hatch so perhaps this particular merkur style razor is more of a standard issue than i understand when i received it in the mail the box was open the head unscrewed and contained only one blade i know thats a shipping thing not a note on the product but perhaps its a note on the packaging im not sure if there were supposed to be more than one blade in the box as noted it was all apart and open when received as for the shave i shave both my face and head and it worked great very smooth compared to the dollar shave club razorsblades i tried out a few months ago which were very dull even with multiple blades in the head so i give it a good review based on shave ascetics price and feel
product: merkur classic  razor double edge saftey razor
